Party of Action has accused the SABC of being partial and silencing alternative voices. eNCA's Silindelo Masikane has the details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The country is gearing up for local government elections, and various political parties want a chance to be heard. Party of Action (POA) has accused the SABC of being biased and silencing alternative voices. READ: SABC workers to down tools The POA descended onto the SABC's television park recently to stage a sit-in. "The public broadcaster has got a duty to provide fair and unbiased political coverage," says POA's Billy Nyaku. The party believes South Africans deserve to hear from all political parties on service delivery issues and COVID-19. Experts say there is a difference between equality and equity. Watch the video above for more details on this story.